How can I use Latex to generate the conjugation of the verb "to be" in different tenses for singular and plural subjects along with example sentences? 
Here's the Latex code to achieve this:
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{booktabs}
\usepackage{array}
\usepackage{multirow}
\newcolumntype{C}{>{\centering\arraybackslash}p{2cm}}
\newcolumntype{L}{>{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{6cm}}
\begin{document}
\begin{table}[h!]
  \centering
  \caption{Conjugation of the verb "to be"}
  \label{tab:conjugation}
  \begin{tabular}{CLCCCCC}
    \toprule
    & & \multicolumn{6}{c}{Tense} \\
    \cmidrule(lr){3-8}
    & & Present & Past & Future & Present Perfect & Past Perfect & Future Perfect \\
    \midrule
    \multirow{6}{*}{\rotatebox[origin=c]{90}{Subject}}
    & I & am & was & will be & have been & had been & will have been \\
    & You & are & were & will be & have been & had been & will have been \\
    & He/She/It & is & was & will be & has been & had been & will have been \\
    & We & are & were & will be & have been & had been & will have been \\
    & You all & are & were & will be & have been & had been & will have been \\
    & They & are & were & will be & have been & had been & will have been \\
    \midrule
    & Example & I am a teacher. & You were at the store. & He will be here tomorrow. & We have been to France. & You all had been studying for hours. & They will have been married for 10 years. \\
    \bottomrule
  \end{tabular}
\end{table}
\end{document}
This Latex code generates a table with the conjugation of the verb "to be" in different tenses for singular and plural subjects along with example sentences. The table is formatted using the booktabs package to make it look professional. The conjugation and example sentences are generated using the multirow and array packages to format the data correctly.

The LaTeX code you provided is a good starting point for creating a table that displays the conjugation of the verb "to be" across different tenses for singular and plural subjects, along with example sentences. Here's a step-by-step explanation and the complete code:

1. **Document Class and Packages**: 
   - The `article` class is chosen for simplicity.
   - `booktabs` is used for aesthetically pleasing horizontal lines in tables.
   - `array` is used for defining new column types with specific alignments.
   - `multirow` is used to span the subject column across multiple rows.

2. **New Column Types**:
   - `C` is defined for centered text with a 2cm width.
   - `L` is defined for left-aligned text with a 6cm width.

3. **Table Layout**:
   - The table is centered and includes a caption and label for referencing.
   - A multi-row entry is used for the "Subject" column.
   - The tense headers span multiple columns for clarity.

4. **Table Content**:
   - Each row corresponds to a subject pronoun (I, You, He/She/It, We, You all, They) with their respective verb forms.
   - Example sentences are provided for each tense in the last row.

